<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-804-274  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 804 274.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Network  Sept 1989 v3 n5 p53(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FDDI: a lightwave data network standard and its applications.andO;(Fiber Distributed Data Interface)(Technology Perspective)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sumner, Eric E.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The development and implementation of high-performance,wide-bandwidth fiber-optic networks based on the Fiber DistributedData Interface (FDDI) standard proposed by ANSI will create a needfor interfaces to IEEE 802.6 metropolitan area network (MAN) andBroadband Integrated Services Digital Network (ISDN) technologies.andO;Factors driving the development of FDDI are high-performanceworkstations and other computers and computationally demandingapplications requiring graphics or high rates and quantities ofdata transfer.andP;  FDDI specifies a 100M-bps data transfer rate on adual-fiber token-ring network.andP;  It includes four protocol layers:physical, media access control, physical media dependent andsystem management.andP;  FDDI offers high reliability and an opensystem architecture.andP;  Potential applications include backbone,front-end and back-end networks.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fiber Distributed Data Interface StandardData CommunicationsSpecificationsFiber OpticsStandardsCommunications Technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>